            The Board of Prison Terms - preserving public safety



                             Attorney Employment

   The Board of Prison Terms seeks attorneys to represent parolees at
   parole revocation hearings and to represent inmates sentenced to life
   with the possibility of parole at suitability hearings. Statewide
   hourly assignments for hearings at correctional facilities and county
   jails are available. $30.00 per hour. Access to the Boards attorney
   packet on our website is currently under construction. A copy of the
   Boards attorney packet can be obtained by contacting: Board of Prison
   Terms, 1515 K Street, 6th Floor. Attention: Attorney Scheduling,
   Sacramento, CA 95814, (916) 324-1924 or by e-mailing your request to
   attysch@bpt.ca.gov.



